This section discusses general topics related to time and time-keeping.
  2.1 What is Time? 2.2 What is UTC? 2.3 Is UTC the same as GMT? 2.4 What happens during a Leap Second?   2.1 What is Time? This quote from a fortune cookie from Edition 7: &ldquo;Time has been invented in the universe so that everything would not happen at once.&rdquo;
There&rsquo;s another interesting relation between time and change: There is no change without the concept of time, and there is no movement without time.

If you are compiling under FreeBSD and see messages in the syslogs that indicate that the ntpd process is trying to use unavailable sched_ calls, it means you are running a kernel that does not have the POSIX scheduling calls enabled.
 You have two choices:  Ignore the messages.     Generate a new kernel, where the kernel configuration file contains the lines:
options	&quot;P1003_1B&quot;options	&quot;_KPOSIX_PRIORITY_SCHEDULING&quot;options	&quot;_KPOSIX_VERSION=199309L&quot;

